cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the design of a new LPWAN protocol stack and its performance evaluation in a real testbed. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper mentions energy consumption and efficiency, which are related to information theory. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper discusses the self-organizing capability and resilience of the proposed protocol stack. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is another possible category as the paper discusses the scalability of LPWAN deployments. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a less likely category as the paper does not focus on security issues, but it may be relevant to the proposed protocol stack.
